This paper deals with the problem of locomotion control for a tensegrity robot, which is a topic that falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper proposes a reinforcement learning approach to solve this problem, which involves optimizing a feedback policy for the robot. This optimization process is done using a hybrid framework that combines optimization and reinforcement learning, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the problem of rough terrain traversal, which requires the robot to adapt its behavior to different environments, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses simulations to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which involves processing visual data, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV).
